# Code Style Guidelines

## Language and Communication
- Only have 1 markdown file called "README.md"
- Do not use emojis in code, comments, or documentation
- Use professional, technical language only
- Avoid casual or informal expressions
- Write clear, concise, and professional text

## Code Comments
- Use standard English without decorative elements
- Focus on technical accuracy and clarity
- Avoid unnecessary embellishments or casual language
- Keep comments professional and informative

## Documentation
- Write in a formal, technical style
- Use proper grammar and punctuation
- Avoid slang, abbreviations, or casual expressions
- Maintain consistency in tone and style

## Examples

### Good Examples
```python
# Process user authentication request
# Handle video generation timeout
# Initialize OpenAI client with API key
```

### Bad Examples
```python
# 🚀 Process user authentication request
# Handle video generation timeout! 
# Initialize OpenAI client with API key ✨
```

## Error Messages
- Use clear, professional language
- Avoid casual expressions or slang
- Provide specific, actionable information
- Maintain consistent tone across all messages

## Variable Names
- Use descriptive, professional names
- Avoid abbreviations unless standard
- Use camelCase or snake_case consistently
- Choose names that clearly indicate purpose